title.narrative: OUTPUT 1: HEALTH STRATEGIES PLANS, BUDGETS AND EVIDENCE GENERATION

description.narrative: By 2022, Federal and Provincial level health-sector strategies, plans and budgets use solid evidence for Universal Health Coverage and Basic Package of Health Services., which contributes to Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, the most at-risk newborns and children are benefiting from integrated newborn, child health interventions and healthy behaviours.
